Refactorings:
- Join Entities and Parts into a Node class - Simplify connections: only one type allowed: going "upwards" (to the predecessors/parents) (Nodes have an order which is important) - Serialisation: create Node and let it apply settings itself using a virtual member function. -> it can change it's serialisation if complex behaviour is needed - Simplify the entities states (no more connected/unconnected) - Activate/Deactive cannot be overridden anymore. On(De)Activate can be used to add behaviour in subclasses
Inserting and removing nodes from the scene graph

Problems in the current entity system implementation:
1) Composed Parts are not possible, only composed Entities 2) A Part Parser can only create parts. In some cases it is desirable that it can create a whole entity subgraph 3) More complex parsing options are needed 4) Simplification never hurts (the current system is too complicated in some places)
Example: handling of 3D models. Simple meshes with one material are handled by VMeshPart. A model is simply a collection of meshes with materials. Thus a VModelPart should be the composition of multiple VMeshPart instances. It's serialisation needs special treatment: only the "top level" node representing the model should be saved and loaded. The creation of it's VMeshParts is implicitly defined by the file 3d model file
